==English==

===Etymology===
From Old French ''(essence de) [[pétrole]]'',  from Medieval Latin ''[[petroleum]]'', from {{Gr.}} '''[[πετρέλαιον]]''' (''petrelaion'') "oil of the rock", from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[πέτρα]]''' (''petra'') "stone, rock" + '''[[έλαιον]]''' (''elaion'') "olive oil, any oily 
substance".

===Pronunciation===
* {{AHD|pĕt'rəl}}, {{IPA|/ˈpetrəl/}}, {{SAMPA|/"petr@l/}}

====Homophones====
*[[petrel]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{UK}} {{AU}} (''New Zealand'') A fluid consisting of a mixture of refined [[petroleum]] [[hydrocarbon]]s, primarily consisting of [[octane]], and commonly used as a motor [[fuel]].

====Synonyms====
* {{US}} [[gasoline]], [[gas]]

